🔁 Variation 9 — Vertex-Disjoint Paths

📘 Problem

Find the maximum number of vertex-disjoint paths from 1 → N (except source and sink).


---

🧠 Trick (IMPORTANT)

Max-flow only handles edges, not vertices.

Solution: Vertex Splitting

For every vertex v:

v_in → v_out (capacity = 1)

All original edges:

u_out → v_in (capacity = ∞)


